google.description: TEN YEARS AGO, I fell in love with a boy. In the blink of an eye, the boy I loved was ripped from me. TEN YEARS LATER, I ran into the boy I had lost. Yet, he's no longer a boy. He's a man. A deeply wounded man. Dustin Adams was once known for his down to earth, care free spirit. He was the well rounded kid with a promising future. Until the girl he loved was yanked from his life. Now, Dustin is known for his distance and the coldness he radiates. He is simply a shell of the boy he once was. Living the Army life, the close calls he's surrounded by daily have done nothing but further harden his heart. Until the girl he once loved reappears in his life. Can what they shared so long ago be restored? Or is Dustin fated to live a life of brokenness?
google.title: Brokenness: a Broken Wings Companion Novel
